This show is just straight up funny. No more needs to be said.

Yet another strong and weird season from my Workaholics bros Anders, Adam and Blake. There are some really strong episodes this season like "Front Yard Wrestling" with a cameo by Ben Stiller and "Blood Drive", and a cameo later in the season by Jack Black and even Booger himself Curtis Armstrong. This is a show like It's Always Sunny In Philadelphia or South Park, where in it's consistently good, humor and style and tone are consistent, and the episodes and writing are fresh and funny. I think one of my favorite episodes of season 5 is "Trivia Pursuit", mainly because of all the '80's references. But I am a product of the 1980's and was raised by T.V. so I guess that makes sense.

 Here we're getting all 13 episodes of season 5, bloopers, deleted scenes, behind the trailer and some more. Hopefully we get the Drunkementary (audio commentary with the cast just getting wrecked while recording, some of the funniest commentary tracks ever recorded), we got screwed out of that on Season 4. *UPDATE: NO DRUNKEMENTARY* Listen, if you're not watching this show, you should be. If you don't like this show, I don't like you. This is a fantastic show, this Blu-ray set is currently $12.99, that's some serious value, buddy. Can't wait for season 6. FULLY APPROVED!
